terraform apply -target="aws_instance.my"

What it does:

applies only the targeted resource
ignores all other resources

Example:

# apply only EC2
terraform apply -target="aws_instance.my"

# apply only VPC
terraform apply -target="aws_vpc.my_vpc"

# apply module
terraform apply -target="module.ec2"

When to use:

testing a single resource    ✅
fixing one broken resource   ✅
partial apply                ✅

⚠️ -target is for troubleshooting only — regular applies should always run against all resources to avoid state drift.
